intro: Seseli libanotis subsp. intermedium, commonly known as the intermediate Lebanon seseli, is a flowering plant belonging to the Apiaceae family. It is characterized by its slender, branching stems and compound leaves with finely divided foliage. The plant produces small, white to pale yellow flowers arranged in umbels, typical of the carrot family. It is native to the Mediterranean region and thrives in rocky or limestone soils. Due to its ornamental value and ecological significance, it is sometimes cultivated in gardens and natural habitats.
